definition: subscription/to subscribe to
to agree/to conclude/to draw up/to subscribe to (a newspaper etc)/to order
to inspect/to review/to read/to peruse/to go through/to experience
RSS (news feeds)
pinyin: ju4 he2 zi1 xun4 ding4 yue4

sentences.english: Spotify offers a number of subscriptions.
Applications can subscribe to push notifications.
sentences.chinese: 应用可以订阅推送通知。

sentences.english: Topics covered include subscribing to the blog and utilizing the different search features. To view the screencast, click here.
sentences.chinese: 涵盖的主题包括如何订阅博客和使用搜索功能。

sentences.english: Reinitializes all subscriptions that have data validation failures.
sentences.chinese: 重新初始化所有存在数据验证失败的订阅。

sentences.english: Hi, thank you for subscribing Greenhill Bookstore e-paper, and we hope all of you enjoy it.
sentences.chinese: 谢谢您订阅格林希尔电子报，希望您会喜欢。

sentences.english: If you send in a subscription on the newspaper, it'll be delivered to your door.
sentences.chinese: 如果你订阅报纸，它会直接给你送上门的。

sentences.english: How Does Bloglines Cure Information Overload?
sentences.chinese: 博客订阅如何处理信息过载？

sentences.english: It defines message exchanges to manipulate subscription resources.
sentences.chinese: 它定义消息交换，以便操作订阅资源。

sentences.english: An option of viewing each of them in detail is given.
sentences.chinese: 提供了一个可以详细查看每个订阅的选项。

sentences.english: The subscription has been marked for reinitialization.
sentences.chinese: 已将订阅标记为重新初始化。

sentences.english: And subscribing to so many print mags is a big waste of paper.
sentences.chinese: 而订阅这么多印刷杂志是一大纸张浪费。

sentences.english: To begin, explore the process you just subscribed to.
sentences.chinese: 开始只导出您想要订阅的流程。

sentences.english: The Timeline service subscribes to all events it is interested in.
sentences.chinese: 时间轴服务订阅其感兴趣的所有事件。
马上订阅，可获2周免费赠阅。

sentences.english: I don’t want to be just another forgettable blog in someone’s feed reader.
sentences.chinese: 我不希望我只是一个被遗忘在订阅单上的博客。

sentences.english: Please submit our subscription to one of the stock market journals.
sentences.chinese: 请将我们的订阅费提交给其中一家股票市场杂志。
